    <p>A company with a conscience. For the last several years, green has been on everyone‚Äôs mind and agenda. We‚Äôre no different. YourMembership has made the switch to a greener environment within our offices &ndash; because we believe that every little bit counts. Every small effort made every day delivers real results. Recycling is paramount, and our Green Team stays on top of it. YourMembership‚Äôs Green Team is a dedicated group of company employees that volunteers to take turns taking out the recyclables! We‚Äôre talking more than aluminum cans &ndash; we have bins for paper products, plastics, cans and more.</p> 
            
    <p>YourMembership has also taken steps to minimize office printing and paper use. Our invoicing and service agreements are 100% electronic. Internal communications are also handled electronically. Even our employee handbook is an e-book! These and other environmentally-aware changes have allowed us to scale back to just two office printers‚Ä¶ which sit by silently most of the day! It‚Äôs green AND quiet.</p>
            
    <p>On a more global scale, from 2007 through 2010 YourMembership contributed each month to the World Wildlife Fund (WWF) on behalf of one of its clients. Now, YourMembership donates to St. Jude Children's Research Hospital. Each month, we recognize a Site of the Month &ndash; one of our wonderful clients that‚Äôs finding great success with YourMembership &ndash; and in recognition of the Site of the Month, we contribute to St. Jude Children‚Äôs Research Hospital in that client‚Äôs name.</p>

    <p><img title="St. Jude Children's Research Hospital" alt="St. Jude Children's Research Hospital logo" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/stjude-logo.jpg" align="right" hspace="20" />St. Jude is recognized world-wide for its pioneering research and treatment of children with cancer and other catastrophic diseases. Founded in 1962 by the late entertainer Danny Thomas, St. Jude freely shares its discoveries with scientific and medical communities around the world, publishing more research articles than any other pediatric cancer research center in the United States. We are thrilled to support this international pediatric treatment and research facility. Winners of our Site of the Month receive patient artwork as a thank you for their donation! </p>

